CONTACT_FORM_TEXT_FIELD_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: How did you hear about us?
TESTIMONIAL_SECTION_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER: Don't just take our word for it - hear from developers who love using our Ethereum transaction monitoring app.
TESTIMONIAL_1_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: EtherView has been a game-changer for tracking new transactions on Ethereum. The real-time alerts and intuitive interface make it easy to stay on top of the latest activity.
TESTIMONIAL_2_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: As an Ethereum developer, having access to a reliable source of new transaction data is crucial. EtherView's robust API and comprehensive filters have streamlined my workflow tremendously.
TESTIMONIAL_3_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: The customizable dashboards and insightful analytics in EtherView have given me a level of transparency into Ethereum transactions that I've never had before. Highly recommended for anyone working with Ethereum data.
FEATURE_1_BODY: Stay ahead of the curve with our innovative feature that allows you to monitor and receive instant notifications for new Ethereum transactions as they occur on the blockchain.
FEATURE_2_BODY: Customize your transaction monitoring experience with robust filtering capabilities. Specify criteria such as wallet addresses, token types, or transaction values to focus on the transactions most relevant to you.
FEATURE_3_BODY: Our seamless integration with popular wallet providers and blockchain explorers ensures a smooth and efficient workflow, allowing you to effortlessly manage and analyze new Ethereum transactions.
FEATURE_4_BODY: Gain invaluable insights into each transaction with our detailed breakdown of essential information, including sender and recipient addresses, transaction values, gas fees, and more.
FEATURE_5_BODY: Built with industry-leading security practices, our platform ensures the utmost protection for your data and transactions, providing you with a reliable and trustworthy solution.
FEATURE_6_BODY: Navigate through our intuitive and user-friendly interface, designed to provide a seamless experience for both novice and experienced users alike, making it easy to track and manage new Ethereum transactions.
PLACEHOLDER_FAQ_TITLE: Frequently Asked Questions About Our Ethereum Transaction Tracking App
ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: Our app connects directly to the Ethereum blockchain and monitors it in real-time for new transactions. As soon as a new transaction is broadcasted, our app will detect and display it for you.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_2: What kind of transaction details are shown?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: You'll see the sender and recipient addresses, the amount of ETH transferred, the transaction fee paid, and the transaction hash which allows you to view it on an Ethereum explorer.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_3: Can I filter or search transactions?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: Yes, you can filter transactions by sender, recipient, amount range, and time period. There is also a search function to look for specific addresses or transaction hashes.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_4: Is there a limit on how many transactions I can view?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: No, our app keeps track of all new Ethereum transactions indefinitely. You'll have access to view and search the full transaction history.
FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Get answers to common questions about monitoring new Ethereum transactions
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: This app allows you to easily track and monitor new transactions occurring on the Ethereum blockchain in real-time.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: The app connects to Ethereum nodes and listens for new blocks being added to the blockchain. When a new block is detected, it parses the transactions and displays them in an easy-to-read list.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_3: What data is shown for each transaction?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: For each new transaction, you can see the sender and receiver addresses, the amount of ETH transferred, the transaction fee paid, and the transaction hash.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_4: Can I filter or search transactions?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: Yes, you can filter transactions by sender, receiver, amount ranges, and more. There is also a search function to look for specific addresses or transaction hashes.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_5: Is there a mobile app version?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: Not at this time, but we are working on mobile app versions for both iOS and Android that will be released soon.
